<h1 id="posting-invoices-with-zero-amount">Posting invoices with zero amount</h1>


<p>In Italy, financial transactions for invoices that have a total amount of 0 (zero) must be posted.</p>
<h2 id="prerequisites">Prerequisites</h2>
<p>Before you can post financial transactions for invoices that have a total amount of 0 (zero), the following prerequisites must be met:</p>
<ul>
<li>The primary address of the legal entity must be in Italy.</li>
<li>In the <strong>Feature management</strong> workspace, turn on the <strong>Posting invoices with zero amount</strong> feature. For more information, see <a href="../../fin-and-ops/get-started/feature-management/feature-management-overview.md">Feature management overview</a>.</li>
</ul>
<h2 id="posting-invoices-that-have-an-amount-of-0-zero">Posting invoices that have an amount of 0 (zero)</h2>
<p>The Posting invoices with zero amount feature applies to invoices that are created in the <strong>Accounts receivable</strong> and <strong>Accounts payable</strong> modules.</p>
<p>When invoices that have an amount of 0 (zero) are posted, the system creates customer/vendor transactions and voucher transactions.</p>
